  "edge_hypothesis": "Williams %R has NEVER been tested as a standalone signal — it was only paired with dead STIFFNESS (which killed the combo, not necessarily WILLR itself). WILLR at -80 boundary detects oversold recovery (transition from selling exhaustion to buying interest) — a transition-detection mechanism using momentum math. EMA200 has been proven to amplify transitional alpha (EMA200 Vortex v2 trans PF=4.321, all-time record). This tests whether EMA200 amplification generalizes beyond Vortex to oscillator-based transition signals. If WILLR crossing -80 captures genuine momentum transitions at the macro trend level (above EMA200 for longs), we discover a new transition-detection family using a completely untested standalone indicator.",
